  <brief_title>Standardized Long Term Follow-up of Patients After Endovascular Embolization of a Brain Aneurysm</brief_title>
  <acronym>ANENDOVASC</acronym>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Fondation Ophtalmologique Adolphe de Rothschild</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Fondation Ophtalmologique Adolphe de Rothschild</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The time-frame and the follow-up elements after embolization of brain aneurysm are not
      standardized. Therefore, few reliable follow-up data are available for these patients.

      This study aims at collecting standardized long term data for these patients, in order to
      assess the occurence of aneurysm recanalization and particularly those requiring another
      intervention on the aneurysm.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
